# ASCII Racing Game

A high-speed racing game with ASCII graphics, featuring multiple car designs, competitive AI, and an immersive racing experience - all in your terminal!

## Features

- **8 Unique Car Designs**: Choose from sports cars, trucks, formula 1, vintage cars, motorcycles, SUVs, convertibles, and futuristic vehicles
- **Large Racing Track**: Race on a wide 8-lane track with a scrolling viewport that follows your car
- **Competitive AI**: Challenge up to 12 AI opponents with varying difficulty levels
- **Practice Mode**: Get comfortable with the controls before the race begins
- **Nitro Boost**: Use nitro for a temporary speed boost when you need it most
- **Collision Detection**: Avoid crashing into other cars
- **High Score System**: Track your best performances
- **Multiple Difficulty Levels**: Easy, Medium, and Hard modes to match your skill level

## Controls

- **W**: Accelerate
- **S**: Brake/Decelerate
- **A**: Move left
- **D**: Move right
- **SPACE**: Activate nitro boost
- **Q**: Quit game

## Gameplay

1. Select your difficulty level
2. Enter your name
3. Choose your car design
4. Start in practice mode to get familiar with controls
5. Race against AI cars to reach the finish line first
6. Avoid collisions with other vehicles
7. Use nitro strategically to gain advantage
8. Try to beat your high score!

## Technical Details

- Written in C++ with standard libraries
- Uses ASCII art for all graphics
- Terminal-based UI with colored text
- Implements game loop with frame-based timing
- Collision detection system
- Viewport scrolling to follow player movement
- AI with randomized behavior patterns

## Requirements

- C++ compiler (supporting C++11 or later)
- Terminal with support for ASCII characters
- Minimum terminal size: 120x40 characters for optimal display

